All the tests in this directory require externally mounted volumes. The tests
use these volumes to setup scylla cluster nodes there in order to test disk
space monitor working.

The volumes can be of any size as the tests pre-create a file with random
content of the size equal to 95% of the volume capacity. Then they ingest
data to reach the critical disk utilization threshold.

The volumes can be created as follow
for i in seq(1,4); then
    mkdir -p testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-$i
    mount -t tmpfs -o size=100M tmpfs testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-$i
done

or simpler
parallel 'mkdir -p testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-{}; sudo mount -t tmpfs -o size=100M tmpfs testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-{}' ::: 1 2 3

The volumes must be then passed to the tests via the custom --space-limited-dirs
argument, e.g.

--space-limited-dirs=testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-1;testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-2;testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-3

or via test.py:
--pytest-arg="--space-limited-dirs testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-1;testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-2;testlog/dev/mnt/scylla-3"
